Theory

Socket Programming

A socket is an endpoint for communication between two machines over a network. It allows data exchange between client and server.

TCP (Transmission Control Protocol)

TCP is a connection-oriented protocol, meaning:

Connection is established before communication
Reliable data transfer
Data arrives in correct order
Error checking and retransmission
Client-Server Model
Server: waits for incoming requests
Client: sends request to server
Steps in TCP Communication
Server creates socket
Server binds IP + port
Server listens for connection
Client connects to server
Data is sent/received
Connection is closed
